MCPs but at the end of the day, he is the worst of the lot. He is a patronising chauvinist who defines what is freedom for women.</p><p>There seems to be no character in Iraivi who bears the streak of resolution. Malar Vizhi (Pooja Devariya), a widow, who leads a polyandrous life, reminiscent of K Balachander's Kalki, might seem like one, but in the end, she is just a cat who is afraid of the water.<br />The dark drama relies heavily on these characters and the emotions, and the perfect cast hasn't betrayed their roles. SJ Suryah's acting skills have finally been put to some terrific use. His eccentric body language fits like a glove for the role of Arul. The director also has an eye for lost talents. In Jigarthanda, he brought Sangili Murugan back to us as 'Petti Kadai Pazhani'. Here we get to see Cheenu Mohan, a long-forgotten brilliant drama actor.</p><p>If Batman is what Gotham needs him to be, then Santhosh Narayanan is what Karthik wants him to be. It's hard to fathom the dedication of a music director who can churn out chartbusters, but composes a song like 'Solla Thudikuthu Manasu', just because the script needs it. From the BGM to the song Dushta, Santhosh has delivered what the film has demanded; nothing less, nothing more.</p><p><br />All said, the film is bit lengthy for its own good. Also, Karthik, who likes to tease the audience with twists, has tried a rather subtle one in Iraivi, which is lost. Also, the rehab scenes of SJ Suryah (which might remind you of the acting course in Jigarthanda) drifts you from the script and makes you impatient.</p><p>Nevertheless, when preachy, over-the-board films masquerade as feminist socials, Karthik's gloomy drama is an honest attempt. It just reflects the raw and hard-hitting reality; it's like Sujatha's Eppothum Penn and Jayakanthan's Sila Nerangalil Sila Manithargal: It is more about the means and little about the end. However, Iraivi demands one thing from 'Manidhi'. It asks her to step out and get drenched in the rain. A step towards the 'virgin future'; the step that Ponni dares.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/DH3iKNTT9-M" mce_src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/DH3iKNTT9-M" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" width="445"></iframe></p>]]></storybody>
